<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="Encoder.php" src="/private/var/www/kw/plugins/w3-total-cache/lib/Minify/HTTP/Encoder.php"><scope doc="Encode and send gzipped/deflated content&#10;&#10;The &quot;Vary: Accept-Encoding&quot; header is sent. If the client allows encoding, &#10;Content-Encoding and Content-Length are added.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;// Send a CSS file, compressed if possible&#10;$he = new HTTP_Encoder(array(&#10;    'content' =&gt; file_get_contents($cssFile)&#10;    ,'type' =&gt; 'text/css'&#10;));&#10;$he-&gt;encode();&#10;$he-&gt;sendAll();&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;// Shortcut to encoding output&#10;header('Content-Type: text/css'); // needed if not HTML&#10;HTTP_Encoder::output($css);&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;// Just sniff for the accepted encoding&#10;$encoding = HTTP_Encoder::getAcceptedEncoding();&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;For more control over headers, use getHeaders() and getData() and send your&#10;own output.&#10;&#10;Note: If you don't need header mgmt, use PHP's native gzencode, gzdeflate, &#10;and gzcompress functions for gzip, deflate, and compress-encoding&#10;respectively.&#10;&#10;@package Minify&#10;@subpackage HTTP&#10;@author Stephen Clay &lt;steve@mrclay.org&gt;" ilk="class" line="46" lineend="297" name="HTTP_Encoder"><variable attributes="public static" citdl="bool" doc="Should the encoder allow HTTP encoding to IE6? &#10;&#10;If you have many IE6 users and the bandwidth savings is worth troubling &#10;some of them, set this to true.&#10;&#10;By default, encoding is only offered to IE7+. When this is true,&#10;getAcceptedEncoding() will return an encoding for IE6 if its user agent&#10;string contains &quot;SV1&quot;. This has been documented in many places as &quot;safe&quot;,&#10;but there seem to be remaining, intermittent encoding bugs in patched &#10;IE6 on the wild web.&#10;&#10;@var bool" line="62" name="encodeToIe6" /><variable attributes="public static" citdl="int" doc="Default compression level for zlib operations&#10;&#10;This level is used if encode() is not given a $compressionLevel&#10;&#10;@var int" line="72" name="compressionLevel" /><scope attributes="public __ctor__" doc="Get an HTTP Encoder object&#10;&#10;@param array $spec options&#10;&#10;'content': (string required) content to be encoded&#10;&#10;'type': (string) if set, the Content-Type header will have this value.&#10;&#10;'method: (string) only set this if you are forcing a particular encoding&#10;method. If not set, the best method will be chosen by getAcceptedEncoding()&#10;The available methods are 'gzip', 'deflate', 'compress', and '' (no&#10;encoding)&#10;&#10;@return null" ilk="function" line="91" lineend="105" name="__construct" returns="null" signature="null __construct(array $spec)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="91" name="spec" /></scope><variable citdl="spec" line="93" name="_content" /><variable citdl="array()" line="101" name="_encodeMethod" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Get content in current form&#10;&#10;Call after encode() for encoded content.&#10;&#10;return string" ilk="function" line="114" lineend="117" name="getContent" returns="this._content" signature="getContent()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Get array of output headers to be sent&#10;&#10;E.g.&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;array(&#10;    'Content-Length' =&gt; '615'&#10;    ,'Content-Encoding' =&gt; 'x-gzip'&#10;    ,'Vary' =&gt; 'Accept-Encoding'&#10;)&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;@return array" ilk="function" line="133" lineend="136" name="getHeaders" returns="array" signature="array getHeaders()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Send output headers&#10;&#10;You must call this before headers are sent and it probably cannot be&#10;used in conjunction with zlib output buffering / mod_gzip. Errors are&#10;not handled purposefully.&#10;&#10;@see getHeaders()&#10;&#10;@return null" ilk="function" line="149" lineend="154" name="sendHeaders" returns="null" signature="null sendHeaders()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="151" name="val" /><variable line="151" name="name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Send output headers and content&#10;&#10;A shortcut for sendHeaders() and echo getContent()&#10;&#10;You must call this before headers are sent and it probably cannot be&#10;used in conjunction with zlib output buffering / mod_gzip. Errors are&#10;not handled purposefully.&#10;&#10;@return null" ilk="function" line="167" lineend="171" name="sendAll" returns="null" signature="null sendAll()" /><scope attributes="public static" doc="Determine the client's best encoding method from the HTTP Accept-Encoding &#10;header.&#10;&#10;If no Accept-Encoding header is set, or the browser is IE before v6 SP2,&#10;this will return ('', ''), the &quot;identity&quot; encoding.&#10;&#10;A syntax-aware scan is done of the Accept-Encoding, so the method must&#10;be non 0. The methods are favored in order of gzip, deflate, then &#10;compress. Deflate is always smallest and generally faster, but is &#10;rarely sent by servers, so client support could be buggier.&#10;&#10;@return array two values, 1st is the actual encoding method, 2nd is the&#10;alias of that method to use in the Content-Encoding header (some browsers&#10;call gzip &quot;x-gzip&quot; etc.)" ilk="function" line="189" lineend="206" name="getAcceptedEncoding" returns="array" signature="array getAcceptedEncoding()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="193" name="_SERVER" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Encode (compress) the content&#10;&#10;If the encode method is '' (none) or compression level is 0, or the 'zlib'&#10;extension isn't loaded, we return false.&#10;&#10;Then the appropriate gz_* function is called to compress the content. If&#10;this fails, false is returned.&#10;&#10;The header &quot;Vary: Accept-Encoding&quot; is added. If encoding is successful, &#10;the Content-Length header is updated, and Content-Encoding is also added.&#10;&#10;@param int $compressionLevel given to zlib functions. If not given, the&#10;class default will be used.&#10;&#10;@return bool success true if the content was actually compressed" ilk="function" line="225" lineend="251" name="encode" returns="bool" signature="bool encode(int $compressionLevel = null)"><variable citdl="int" default="null" ilk="argument" line="225" name="compressionLevel" /><variable citdl="gzdeflate()" line="238" name="encoded" /></scope><scope attributes="public static" doc="Encode and send appropriate headers and content&#10;&#10;This is a convenience method for common use of the class&#10;&#10;@param string $content&#10;&#10;@param int $compressionLevel given to zlib functions. If not given, the&#10;class default will be used.&#10;&#10;@return bool success true if the content was actually compressed" ilk="function" line="265" lineend="274" name="output" returns="bool" signature="bool output(string $content, int $compressionLevel = null)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="265" name="content" /><variable citdl="int" default="null" ilk="argument" line="265" name="compressionLevel" /><variable citdl="HTTP_Encoder" line="270" name="he" /><variable citdl="he.encode()" line="271" name="ret" /></scope><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array()" line="277" name="_headers" /><scope attributes="protected static" doc="Is the browser an IE version earlier than 6 SP2?" ilk="function" line="283" lineend="296" name="_isBuggyIe" returns="boolean" signature="_isBuggyIe()"><variable citdl="int" line="292" name="version" /><variable citdl="_SERVER" line="285" name="ua" /></scope></scope></scope>